{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" process that owns the VM.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"text":") read the PID file to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"PID File Lifecycle","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" detects stale PID files by checking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"anchor":"Type-Properties","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name